==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[efflorescere]]'' - ''ex'', out, ''[[florescere]]'', to blossom

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{chemistry}} The formation of a powdery [[surface]] on [[crystal]]s, as a [[hydrate]] is converted to [[anhydrous]] form by losing loosely [[bound]] [[water of crystallization]] to the [[atmosphere]].
# {{botany}} The production of [[flower]]s.
# (''metaphorical'') Rapid flowering of a [[culture]] or [[civilisation]] etc.
# {{pathology}} A [[red]]ness, [[rash]], or [[erupt]]ion on the [[skin]].

